&lt;p&gt;Our team is a multidisciplinary group of hardware, embedded software, and AI engineers dedicated to creating innovative wearable electronic products. We combine deep technical expertise and passion for technology to bring ideas from early concept to production.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Might Do:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the electrical system design of a wearable device, including system architecture, power management, MCU/SoC selection, and sensor integration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead Schematic design, PCB layout, bringup, and test using a combination of internal teams and external partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with SME teams to integrate audio, camera, wireless (Wi-Fi/Bluetooth), and charging systems into a compact, low-power form factor.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use data to drive technical trade-offs, component selection, comms and system bus strategies, power strategies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor and guide junior engineers and technical program managers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Requires Bachelors or Masters of Science degree in Electrical Engineering, Computer Science, or Physics, or a related field; advanced degree preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of experience in electrical engineering and system architecture.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise leading low-power consumer or medical electronic systems through all stages from concept to production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Circuit fundamentals understanding ranging from low power analog to high speed signals. Intimate familiarity with EE processes and Cadence schematic and layout tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep knowledge in at least one adjacent subsystem such as acoustic, battery, power, sensing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading engineering teams in a cross-functional and fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with ODM teams to bring a consumer electronic or medical device from concept to production.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication experience building technical documentation and presentations to represent status and decisions to leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
